Name: Denmark National Bank Discount Rate
Metadata: Definition: The official discount rate is charged for drawings against the first tranche of bank loans from the Central Bank. The charge for drawings against the second tranche is the official discount rate plus 3 percentage points.  Sources: Statistiske Department, Statistisk Arbog, Copenhagen: Statistiske Dept. (1864-1918), League of Nations (1919-45), Danmarks Bank, Monetary Review (1946-) Notes: Data are quarterly from 1864 through 1877 and monthly thereafter.
